l/440))\\n    26→- Git hooks are now a no-op if Entire is not enabled in the repo ([#445](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/445))\\n    27→- Resume sessions now sorted by creation time ascending ([#447](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/447))\\n    28→\\n    29→### Fixed\\n    30→\\n    31→- Secret redaction hardened across all checkpoint persistence paths ([#395](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/395))\\n    32→- Gemini session restore following latest Gemini pattern ([#403](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/403))\\n    33→- Transcript path stored in checkpoint metadata breaking location independence ([#403](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/403))\\n    34→- Integration tests hanging on machines with a TTY ([#414](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/414))\\n    35→- Stale ACTIVE/IDLE/ENDED sessions incorrectly condensed into every commit ([#418](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/418))\\n    36→- Gemini TTY handling when called as a hook ([#430](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/430))\\n    37→- Deselected agents reappearing as pre-selected on re-enable ([#443](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/443))\\n    38→- UTF-8 truncation producing garbled text for CJK/emoji characters ([#444](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/444))\\n    39→- Git refs resembling CLI flags causing errors ([#446](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/446))\\n    40→- Over-aggressive secret redaction in session transcripts ([#471](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/471))\\n    41→\\n    42→### Docs\\n    43→\\n    44→- Security and privacy documentation ([#398](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/398))\\n    45→- Agent integration checklist for validating new agent integrations ([#442](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/442))\\n    46→- Clarified README wording and agent-agnostic troubleshooting ([#453](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/453))\\n    47→\\n    48→### Thanks\\n    49→\\n    50→Thanks to @AlienKevin for contributing to this release!\\n    51→\\n   